        "text": "Yes. Two blocks of identical area in the same Brisbane suburb can sell at meaningfully different prices because of shape. A regular rectangle with a usable frontage, level grade and a logical building envelope is worth more than an irregular, narrow, or battle-axe block of the same square-metre figure. Buyers, valuers, and developers all adjust for shape. The adjustment is rarely listed on a sales sheet but it is built into the price the market clears at."
      }
